The US government should lift the travel advisory it issued to its citizens against visiting Kenya, Tourism CS Najib Balala has said. Speaking in Mombas, Balala said the was unjustified, citing the reduction of terrorist attacks in the region"The government has invested heavily in improving the the country's security and managed to minimize terror threats in the country,"Balala said. In the advisory, the United States warned its citizens against visiting Kenya's Coast and Northeastern region, citing terror attack threats by Al-Shabaab and high crime rates